“Ancestors”

There are moments, before I press the shutter, I see the final image in my mind. Like it was already out in the otherworld, waiting to be made physical. This was one of those moments

That evening, I looked down into the valley as mist and fog parted revealing trees that seemed to stand in challenge against the arduous passage of time.

My SuperRare Genesis and first nft ever, available now.

“Goblin Palace”

Ok, real talk. This year was hard.

I barely went out to shoot, which a big chunk of why I haven’t really posted here. I didn’t want to retread old shots over and over and over. 

While this year was hard and I barely shot, I’m really proud of the movements I made in therapy this year.  I can honestly say I loved mountains this year in healing myself and moving forward. To me, that’s priceless. 

Also, I upgraded my camera to the Sony a7r5 so that’s pretty damn awesome. 

This shot is one of the times I went out. I drove to Utah and Goblin Valley State Park with two people who I am honored to calm close friends. @autpops & @nateinthewild 

Next year I’ll be pushing myself to get out and shoot more so you’ll be seeing me in 2023. 

I hope you all find solace and joy and prosperity and love in 2023. May your thoughts, feelings, and imagination help shape the reality you want to live in.

“The Dreaming Tree”

Taken at the Ancient Bristlecone Pine Forest in the White Mountains of eastern California. This tree has stood since the end of the Stone Age/beginning of the Bronze Age. Existing between the physical and spiritual worlds, the world of dreams is where we can let our unconscious free itself from the riggers our of lives. This is where the Dreaming Tree resides.

“Sister Moon, will be my guide
In your blue, blue shadows, I would hide

I'm all by myself, in your silver light
I would gaze at your face the whole night through
I'd go out of my mind, but for you”

I was at Rainier last night working on some shots for a future composite when my friend tapped me on the shoulder and said “look left.” And there She was, rising over the cascades.
